<h1>Tips for Finding Textbooks!</h1><p>While sifting through the endless posts on the site, it might be the case that you can&#39;t find exactly what you&#39;re looking for.&nbsp; Never fear!&nbsp; For your benefit, we listed a few places that can help you find the best deal on the texts you need.</p><ul>	<li><a href="http://www.half.ebay.com/textbooks" target="_blank">Half.com</a> - run by eBay.&nbsp; Most of the textbooks are sold by smaller 	companies or individuals.</li>	<li><a href="http://www.amazon.com/New-Used-Textbooks-Books/b?ie=UTF8&node=465600" target="_blank">Amazon.com</a> - good for finding new books (and other things)</li>	<li><a href="http://www.bkstr.com/Home/10001-10236-1?demoKey=d" target="_blank">eFollett.com</a> - the online presence of our campus bookstore.</li>	<li><a href="http://books.shop.ebay.com/Textbooks-Education-/2228/i.html" target="_blank">eBay.com</a> - helpful for finding cheap Eastern Economy editions of texts 	(legal to own here in the states, but most often found in paperback form)</li></ul><p>Also, speak with your floor&#39;s TOME representative (if your floor has one) to see what texts they have.&nbsp; Sometimes you&#39;ll get lucky and won&#39;t have to pay anything for your text!&nbsp; Don&#39;t get your hopes up, though.</p>